jwo.landserf.gui
Class GISFrameAdapter

java.lang.Object
  jwo.landserf.gui.GISFrameAdapter
All Implemented Interfaces:
GISFrame
Direct Known Subclasses:
SimpleGISFrame
public class GISFrameAdapter
extends Object
implements GISFrame

An adapter class for creating GISFrames. The methods in this class are empty. This class exists as convenience for GISFrames. Extend this class to create a GISFrame and override the methods for the behaviour of interest.

Version:
2.3, 25th September, 2005.
Author:
Jo Wood.

getPrintUtilities

public PrintUtilities getPrintUtilities()
Would pass on the printer utilities from the frame, but ignored in this case. When implemented fully, if the utilities have not been initialised, they should be at this point. This is used since printer initialisation can be expensive so is better passed by reference rather than recreated.

Specified by:
getPrintUtilities in interface GISFrame
Returns:
Set of printer utilities for printing, previewing and storing printer settings. Always returns null in this adapter.
